The range of possible pid values using constants MIN_PID=300 and MAX_PID=5000.

int allocate_map(void) function with no parameters and return type int. It will initialize all pids from MIN_PID to MAX_PID to 0 using any data structure.
It will return 1 after completion.

int allocate_pid(void) function with no parameters and return type int. It will allocate 1 pid by assigning it to 1 and an active process. 
It will return the pid after completion or -1 if all pids are in use. 

void release_pid(int_pid) function with int_pid as its parameter and void return type. It will release 1 pid and reset it to 0 to be able to be allocated to a new process. no error etc
